      <originalsloc id="aspace_3ba322d01963be533f707f00d449064d">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 265) and in the Ralph Patteson Cobbold Papers (MS 1663).   The papers consist of two manuscript journals recounting the campaign against Maxamad Cabdulle Xasan, the "Mad Mullah of Somaliland," from March 19 to August 5, 1903. Cobbold describes the sufferings on the march, the heat, the lack of palatable food, native customs, intelligence reports from escaped prisoners of the Mullah, details of the Italian campaign against the Mullah, reports of casualties, and skirmishes and rumors of a disastrous defeat of the British force. Preceding the journal is Cobbold's retained copy of a letter written by him at the end of January 1903 describing the plans for disembarking troops and proceeding against the Mullah.</p>  
